g" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678538551220" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678538551220"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>In training blocks, these three training sessions can be repeated twice per week with only one day left to rest and recover. However, during the season, you may opt to do them only once and to go for a schedule thatâ€™s like - Monday; Wednesday; or Friday, so you have a rest day between each workout. Itâ€™s vital to remember that along with strength training, boxers will typically have to find time for a boxing session, some aerobic conditioning, and, of course, recovery. And so, if at any point, you feel too tired or you feel like your body canâ€™t take yet another heavy session, then itâ€™s a good idea to either scale the workout or to just altogether skip it.&nbsp;</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783761053" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783761053"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Basic Equipment You Need</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783769284" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783769284"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>You donâ€™t need to have a ton of equipment in order to do boxing strength training. However, there are still some essential items that you need access to in order for the sessions to be as effective as possible.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678717190038" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678717190038"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Resistance Bands</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678717190701" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678717190701"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The resistance band is an incredibly useful piece of equipment that is used to make various â€œeasyâ€ exercises harder. It can be used to make push-ups, pull-ups, and squats more effective, and itâ€™s also terrific for doing mobility work.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783790731" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783790731"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Olympic Weightlifting Barbell&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783791280" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783791280"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The Olympic weightlifting barbell is considered the standard for doing exercises such as the <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/guides/snatch" class="">snatch</a>, the squat, the deadlift, and the bench press. Considering that all those are present in a boxing strength training routine, itâ€™s easy to understand why this barbell is considered an essential item. On the market, you will find tons of weightlifting bars; however, you need to look for ones that match the exact dimensions required. Those are 45 pounds in weight and 7 feet long.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679232070545" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1679232070545" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fada7de8-3ec5-46c4-977a-25036ad105ee/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/WBCM-Oleksandr-Usik-Bench-Press.jpeg" alt="WBCM Oleksandr Usik Bench Press" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1280" height="854" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Oleksandr Usik Bench Press" natural-width="1280" natural-height="854"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783806776" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783806776"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Free Weights&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783807394" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783807394"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Along with the barbell, you also need weight plates that you can add to it in order to increase the weight. As this is training for boxing, you wonâ€™t need that many plates. Typically, you need a few 5lbs, 10lbs, 25lbs, and maybe 35lbs at most. Thatâ€™s because the strength training boxing workouts are almost never focused on you lifting as much weight as you can but more so on building explosiveness and power, which is why you donâ€™t need to get a ton of weights or the heaviest plates available.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783822083" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783822083"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Dumbbells</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783822615" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783822615"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Here, you can opt for getting various dumbbells of different weights, or you can just opt for the ones that allow you to change the plates and add/remove weight. Along with that, nowadays, there are dumbbells with automatic weight-changing that are much more convenient for a home or garage gym.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783840897" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783840897"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Squat Rack&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783841500" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783841500"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg